Introduction to Earn Value Management \
\
\pard\pardeftab560\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The development of metrics on Project Management is quite an effort to a company. This is quite a challenge  to a small company since the measuring process takes a lot of time of the resources. This is why some Project Managers (PMPs) think that calculating this metrics are only useful for projects with more than 100 people involved.\
However, it\'92s not that simple, since there are organizations that can have projects that cost millions with a very small team, or in a very short time, and a minor deviation on scope can jeopardize more than the project itself.\
\
Metrics are like compass for projects, they don\'92t decide or judge but they help on guidance and they are directly proportional to project risk, they become more important as the project risk rises. C-Levels often require some qualified information  for crucial decisions. Some decisions can be \'93C-Level killers\'94 like change management decisions. Support this actions with no information on the background or worst, wrong one, are certainly the same as declaring a \'93manager funeral\'94.\
