\f2\b \cf2 Project Management Technology Quotient (PMTQ)\
\pard\pardeftab560\qj\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 \
\
\
\
According to Project Management syntax, KPIs are created through calculation of Earn Value Management Systems (EVMS). EVM consist in a group of metrics that use resources project time and cost. This measurements supposed to help the communication, but it\'92s not a decision maker. If well interpreted can give a productive forecast for the course of the project. The challenge in measuring performance is very painful for companies even with software support with a time clock integration. \
\
\'93No leader is oblivious to digital disruption!\'94 (PMI, 2019). To raise the level of PMTQ (Project Management Technology Quotient), EVM must be simple and fluent among the teams and its project execution. In summary, a project plan has no control capacity of measurement efficiency, costs or effectiveness during its execution, if it doesn\'92t measure through time while it\'92s being executed.\
\
Project management performance requires planning just like any other knowledge area, not all metrics should count and not all procedures need to be taken care, but as all good projects it demands a good planning that are influence from size of the team, size of the project, cost of the project, risk of the project, and so on.\
\
In the days of today, it\'92s important to add the \'93digital\'94 as an important tool for decision-makers and raise the level of PMTQ of their organization. Therefore, an organization should have a PMO well supported in order to adapt to all environments as expected. \
This means essential outputs such as templates of projects should be created on a global form and published not only as pre-plans but also the projects executed so that all organizations, in a whole, should \'93lessons learned\'94 together on how to improve their working system.\
\
PMTQ at maximum level requires that the company members have some knowledge of all their enterprise process and have friendly technology that can support it at organizational level.\
